{"title_page": "2018 nine-pin bowling Single's World Championships \u2013 Men's sprint", "text_new": "{{Infobox sports competition event\n| event         = Men's sprint\n| competition   = 2018 nine-pin bowling<br>Single's World Championships\n| image         = [[File:Bowling pictogram.svg|80px]]\n| location      = [[Cluj-Napoca]], [[Romania]]\n| dates         = 23 May 2018\n| competitors   = 32\n| nations       = 16\n| gold          = {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Vilmo\u0161 Zavarko]]\n| silver        = {{flagicon|GER}} Axel Schondelmaier\n| bronze        = {{flagicon|ITA}} Wolfgang Blaas\n| bronze2       = {{flagicon|ROU}} Nicolae Lupu\n}}\n{{2018 nine-pin bowling Single's World Championships events}}\nThe '''men's sprint''' event at the [[2018 nine-pin bowling Single's World Championships]] was held in [[Cluj-Napoca]], [[Romania]] on 23 May 2018.\n<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://wnba-nbc.de/Sport/Weltmeisterschaften/WM-2018-Cluj/2018-Cluj-WCC-Single-Schedule-2018-01-09.pdf|title=2018 Single's World Championships schedule}}</ref>\n\nThe title of world champion was successfully defended by Serbian [[Vilmo\u0161 Zavarko]], who defeated German Axel Schondelmaier in the final. Bronze medals went to semi-finalists Italian Wolfgang Blass and representative of the hosts - Romanian Nicolae Lupu.\n\n== Results ==\n\n=== Starting places ===\n\nThe starting places have been allocated on the basis of each team's achievements during the previous championships.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!\n!{{Flagicon|AUT}} <br />AUT\n!{{Flagicon|BIH}} <br />BIH\n!{{Flagicon|CRO}} <br />CRO\n!{{Flagicon|CZE}} <br />CZE\n!{{Flagicon|DEN}} <br />DEN\n!{{Flagicon|EST}} <br />EST\n!{{Flagicon|FRA}} <br />FRA\n!{{Flagicon|GER}} <br />GER\n!{{Flagicon|HUN}} <br />HUN\n!{{Flagicon|ITA}} <br />ITA\n!{{Flagicon|MKD}} <br />MKD\n!{{Flagicon|POL}} <br />POL\n!{{Flagicon|ROU}} <br />ROU\n!{{Flagicon|SLO}} <br />SLO\n!{{Flagicon|SRB}} <br />SRB\n!{{Flagicon|SVK}} <br />SVK\n! Total\n|-align=\"center\"\n! Number of seeds\n| 1 || 1 || 2 || 2 || 1 || 1 || 2 || 1 || 1 || 1 || 1 || 2 || 3 || 3 || 3 || 3 || '''32''' \n|}\n\n=== Draw ===\n\nThe players were drawn into pairs with the reservation that competitors from the same country can not play in the first round against each other.\n<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://wnba-nbc.de/2018-Single-Sprint-Startplan1.pdf|title=Sprint schedule 1}}</ref>\n<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://wnba-nbc.de/Sport/Weltmeisterschaften/WM-2018-Cluj/VII_-WM-Single/2018-Single-Sprint-Startplan2.pdf|title=Sprint schedule 2}}</ref>\n<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://wnba-nbc.de/Sport/Weltmeisterschaften/WM-2018-Cluj/VII_-WM-Single/2018-Single-Sprint-m-Tabelle.pdf|title=Sprint draw with results}}</ref>\n\n{{32TeamBracket-9pins\n| RD1  =  '''Round of 32'''\n| RD2  =  '''Round of 16'''\n| RD3  =  '''Quarterfinals'''\n| RD4  =  '''Semifinals'''\n| RD5  =  '''Final'''\n\n<!-- Round of 32 -->\n| RD1-seed01     =\n| RD1-team01     = {{flagicon|HUN}} Tam\u00e1s Kiss\n| RD1-score0101  = 0\n| RD1-score0102  = \n| RD1-seed02     =\n| RD1-team02     = {{flagicon|AUT}} '''Philipp Vsetecka'''\n| RD1-score0201  = '''2'''\n| RD1-score0202  =\n\n| RD1-seed03     =\n| RD1-team03     = {{flagicon|GER}} '''Timo Hoffmann'''\n| RD1-score0301  = '''2'''\n| RD1-score0302  = \n| RD1-seed04     =\n| RD1-team04     = {{flagicon|SLO}} Gregor Baj\u017eelj\n| RD1-score0401  = 0\n| RD1-score0402  =\n\n| RD1-seed05     =\n| RD1-team05     = {{flagicon|AUT}} Lukas Huber\n| RD1-score0501  = 0\n| RD1-score0502  = \n| RD1-seed06     =\n| RD1-team06     = {{flagicon|POL}} '''Micha\u0142 Szulc'''\n| RD1-score0601  = '''2'''\n| RD1-score0602  =\n\n| RD1-seed07     =\n| RD1-team07     = {{flagicon|SLO}} Matej Lepej\n| RD1-score0701  = 1 \n| RD1-score0702  = 18\n| RD1-seed08     =\n| RD1-team08     = {{flagicon|ITA}} '''Wolfgang Blaas'''\n| RD1-score0801  = 1\n| RD1-score0802  = '''19'''\n\n| RD1-seed09     =\n| RD1-team09     = {{flagicon|CZE}} '''Jan B\u00edna'''\n| RD1-score0901  = 1\n| RD1-score0902  = '''21'''\n| RD1-s