{"title_page": "Paek Hak-rim", "text_new": "{{Korean name|Paek}}\n{{no footnotes|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = <!-- include middle initial, if not specified in birth_name -->\n| image         = Paek_Hak-rim_portrait.jpg<!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date    = 1918<!-- {{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Birth-date and age|birth date\u2020}} for living people supply only the year unless the exact date is already widely published, as per [[WP:DOB]] -->\n| birth_place   = [[South Pyongan Province]], [[Japanese Korea]]\n| death_date    = October 5, 2006 (aged 87\u201388)<!-- {{Death date and age|2006|10|05|1918|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|death date\u2020|birth date\u2020}}  -->\n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = \n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = \n| years_active  =\n| known_for     = \n| notable_works =\n| module=\n{{Infobox Korean name|context=north|\nhangul=\ubc31\ud559\ub9bc|\nhanja=\u767d\u9db4\u6797|\nmr=Paek Hakrim|\nrr=Baek Hak-rim|child=yes\n}}\n}}\n'''Paek Hak-rim''' (1918 \u2013 October 5, 2006) was the Deputy Director of the [[North Korea]]n [[Ministry of Public Security of North Korea|Ministry of Public Security]].  He occupied a number of high-ranking positions, including serving from 1998 to 2003 on the [[National Defense Commission of North Korea|National Defense Commission]]. He was also the [[Ministry of People's Security|Minister of People's Security]] from 1998 to 2003.\n\n==Biography==\nPaek was born in [[South Pyongan Province]], and served in the guerrilla armies of the [[Korean independence movement]] before 1945.  He also served in the North Korean army after independence, reaching the rank of Major General in 1958 and Lieutenant General in 1962. He became Vice Marshal in 1992.\n\nHe has been a delegate to the [[Supreme People's Assembly]] following the [[1967 North Korean parliamentary election|4th]] (1967), [[1982 North Korean parliamentary election|7th]] (1982), [[1986 North Korean parliamentary election|8th]] (1986), [[1990 North Korean parliamentary election|9th]] (1990), [[19*/ North Korean parliamentary election|10th]] (1998), and [[2003 North Korean parliamentary election|11th]] (2003) elections. He joined the [[Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea|Central Committee]] of the [[Workers' Party of Korea]] in 1970, and served on that body continuously beginning in 1980. In 1998 he was appointed to the [[Ministry of People's Security|Minister of People's Security]], a position he held until July 2003.<ref>[https://books.google.pl/books?id=xpu6NUONT80C&pg=PA239&lpg=PA239&dq=Ri+Il-hwan&source=bl&ots=75nDaFp41N&sig=ACfU3U1Klzqh4MFLXMvVLP-Kij4OL8C4Vw&hl=pl&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjUq_P6oefoAhWOWhUIHeB7CnUQ6AEwBHoECBQQMg#v=onepage&q=Ri%20Il-hwan&f=false North Korea Under Kim Chong-il: Power, Politics, and Prospects for Change, p. 23]</ref>\n\nPaek died of a brain hemorrhage on at 2 PM on October 5, 2006.  The following day a wreath was sent to his funeral by [[Kim Jong-il]], and laudatory obituaries were distributed through the [[North Korean media]].\n\n==Works==\n*{{cite book|author=Paek Hak-rim|title=As He Leads the Revolution, for the Freedom and Liberation of the People|year=1977|publisher=Foreign Languages Publishing House|location=Pyongyang|oclc=6198041|chapter=On Our Way to the Homeland}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|North Korea}}\n*[[Politics of North Korea]]\n\n==References==\n*Yonhap News Agency.  \"Who's who, North Korea,\" pp.&nbsp;787\u2013812 in {{cite book|author=Yonhap News Agency|year=2004|title=Korea Annual 2004|location=Seoul | publisher=Author|isbn=89-7433-070-9}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.kcna.co.jp/item/2006/200610/news10/07.htm|title=Past News: Vice Marshal Paek Hak Rim Dies|date=2006-10-06|accessdate=2007-05-22|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071010055536/http://www.kcna.co.jp/item/2006/200610/news10/07.htm|archivedate=2007-10-10}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20050113031019/http://nk.chosun.com/english/database/database.html?ACT=p_detail&id=62 NKChosun profile]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=?}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Ministry of People's Security|Minister of People's Security]]|years=1998\u20132003}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Choe Ryong-su]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Paek, Hak-rim}}\n[[Category:1918 births]]\n[[Category:2006 deaths]]\n[[Category:Members of the Supreme People's Assembly]]\n[[Category:People from South Pyongan]]\n[[Category:Workers' Party of Korea politicians]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of North Korea]]\n\n\n{{NorthKorea-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Korean name|Paek}}\n{{no footnotes|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = <!-- include middle initial, if not specified in birth_name -->\n| image         = Paek_Hak-rim_portrait.jpg<!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date    = 1918<!-- {{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Birth-date and age|birth date\u2020}} for living people supply only the year unless the exact date is already widely published, as per [[WP:DOB]] -->\n| birth_place   = [[South Pyongan Province]], [[Japanese Korea]]\n| death_date    = October 5, 2006 (aged 87\u201388)<!-- {{Death date and age|2006|10|05|1918|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|death date\u2020|birth date\u2020}}  -->\n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = \n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = \n| years_active  =\n| known_for     = \n| notable_works =\n| module=\n{{Infobox Korean name|context=north|\nhangul=\ubc31\ud559\ub9bc|\nhanja=\u767d\u9db4\u6797|\nmr=Paek Hakrim|\nrr=Baek Hak-rim|child=yes\n}}\n}}\n'''Paek Hak-rim''' (1918 \u2013 October 5, 2006) was the Deputy Director of the [[North Korea]]n [[Ministry of Public Security of North Korea|Ministry of Public Security]].  He occupied a number of high-ranking positions, including serving from 1998 to 2003 on the [[National Defense Commission of North Korea|National Defense Commission]]. He was also the [[Ministry of People's Security|Minister of People's Security]] from 1998 to 2003.\n\n==Biography==\nPaek was born in [[South Pyongan Province]], and served in the guerrilla armies of the [[Korean independence movement]] before 1945.  He also served in the North Korean army after independence, reaching the rank of Major General in 1958 and Lieutenant General in 1962. He became Vice Marshal in 1992.\n\nHe has been a delegate to the [[Supreme People's Assembly]] following the [[1967 North Korean parliamentary election|4th]] (1967), [[1982 North Korean parliamentary election|7th]] (1982), [[1986 North Korean parliamentary election|8th]] (1986), [[1990 North Korean parliamentary election|9th]] (1990), [[19*/ North Korean parliamentary election|10th]] (1998), and [[2003 North Korean parliamentary election|11th]] (2003) elections. He joined the [[Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea|Central Committee]] of the [[Workers' Party of Korea]] in 1970, and served on that body continuously beginning in 1980. In 1998 he was appointed to the [[Ministry of People's Security|Minister of People's Security]], a position he held until July 2003.<ref>[https://books.google.pl/books?id=xpu6NUONT80C&pg=PA239&lpg=PA239&dq=Ri+Il-hwan&source=bl&ots=75nDaFp41N&sig=ACfU3U1Klzqh4MFLXMvVLP-Kij4OL8C4Vw&hl=pl&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjUq_P6oefoAhWOWhUIHeB7CnUQ6AEwBHoECBQQMg#v=onepage&q=Ri%20Il-hwan&f=false North Korea Under Kim Chong-il: Power, Politics, and Prospects for Change, p. 23]</ref>\n\nPaek died of a brain hemorrhage on at 2 PM on October 5, 2006.  The following day a wreath was sent to his funeral by [[Kim Jong-il]], and laudatory obituaries were distributed through the [[North Korean media]].\n\n==Works==\n*{{cite book|author=Paek Hak-rim|title=As He Leads the Revolution, for the Freedom and Liberation of the People|year=1977|publisher=Foreign Languages Publishing House|location=Pyongyang|oclc=6198041|chapter=On Our Way to the Homeland}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|North Korea}}\n*[[Politics of North Korea]]\n\n==References==\n*Yonhap News Agency.  \"Who's who, North Korea,\" pp.&nbsp;787\u2013812 in {{cite book|author=Yonhap News Agency|year=2004|title=Korea Annual 2004|location=Seoul | publisher=Author|isbn=89-7433-070-9}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.kcna.co.jp/item/2006/200610/news10/07.htm|title=Past News: Vice Marshal Paek Hak Rim Dies|date=2006-10-06|accessdate=2007-05-22|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071010055536/http://www.kcna.co.jp/item/2006/200610/news10/07.htm|archivedate=2007-10-10}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20050113031019/http://nk.chosun.com/english/database/database.html?ACT=p_detail&id=62 NKChosun profile]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=?}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Ministry of People's Security|Minister of People's Security]]|years=2003\u20132004}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Choe Ryong-su]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Paek, Hak-rim}}\n[[Category:1918 births]]\n[[Category:2006 deaths]]\n[[Category:Members of the Supreme People's Assembly]]\n[[Category:People from South Pyongan]]\n[[Category:Workers' Party of Korea politicians]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of North Korea]]\n\n\n{{NorthKorea-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rakoon", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paek_Hak-rim"}
